        <td width="3%" class="style9">
          <b>S.No.</b>
        </td>
        <td width="10%" class="style9">
          <b>Title</b>
        </td>
        <td width="55%" class="style9">
          <b>Description</b>
        </td>
        <td width="27%" class="style9">
          <b>Refer to Clause</b>
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td width="3%" class="style9">1</td>
        <td width="10%" class="style9">Product Name</td>
        <td width="55%" class="style9">OPTIONAL TRAVEL INSURANCE FOR E-TICKET PASSENGERS</td>
        <td width="27%" class="style9"> </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td width="3%" class="style9">2</td>
        <td width="10%" class="style9">What am I covered for</td>
        <td width="55%" class="style9">
          <ol>
            <li>
	Accidental injury leading to Death, Permanent total disability, Permanent partial disability during the trip.
	 <ul style="list-style-type:disc"><li>If the insured person dies as a result of the accident within 12 months of its occurrence, or thereafter for any other covered reason, and a claim for permanent impairment had been made prior to the death, then payment will be made of the sum insured less any sum paid for the permanent impairment, and any sum that was due to be paid for the permanent impairment shall not be paid.</li><li>If the insured person is not found within 7 years of the disappearance, sinking or wrecking of the scheduled railway carrier in which he was travelling as a fare paying passenger, the insured person will be presumed to have died as a result of the accident.</li></ul></li>
            <li>Hospitalisation expenses for Injury during the trip</li>
            <li>Cost of transportation of mortal remains in the event of death during the trip. </li>
            <li>Coverage shall begin from the actual boarding of the train to the actual arrival of train at the destination stations including the process of entraining and detraining  </li>
          </ol>
        </td>
        <td width="27%" class="style9">Part II of the Schedule</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td width="3%" class="style9">3</td>
        <td width="15%" class="style9">What are the major exclusions in the policy</td>
        <td width="55%" class="style9">
          <ol>
            <li>Accident while crossing the railway tracks.</li>
            <li>Claim arising or resulting from Insured committing any breach of law with criminal intent</li>
            <li>Accident under influence of intoxicating liquor or drugs </li>
            <li>Intentional self injury, suicide or attempted suicide</li>
            <li>Any natural cause or disease or medical or surgical treatment unless such treatment becomes necessary due to injury caused by the said untoward incident</li>
            <li>Claim in instances where ticket was booked but train was not boarded</li>
            <li>Claim in instances where ticket was booked, but the ticket was not confirmed</li>
            <li>Treatment of any illness even if caused by Accident or untoward incident suffered by insured except any caused by accident or untoward incident and requiring immediate medical treatment in order to maintain life or relieve immediate pain or distress</li>
            <li>Compensation under more than one of the foregoing benefits in respect of same accident or period of disablement of the insured</li>
          </ol>
      (Note: The above mentioned is a partial listing of the policy exclusions. Please refer to the policy wordings for the full listing)
    </td>
        <td width="27%" class="style9">Part II of the Schedule and Exclusions Applicable  to respective benefits</td>
      </tr>
